arStrings.szText: I'm not sure how to thank you, my friend.
Edgar surprised in spite of himself to realize there are still good people out there fighting for justice.
I can't stop trying to make up for the deaths I've caused. I thought I could just hide people outside the city for a while, wait for things to blow over, but now...I fear for Caldeum.
Wistful - a long journey is over, but there is little satisfaction in it - too many good people are dead.
I'm going to take some people to Gea Kul, maybe get on a boat myself, disappear for a while.
Here, I want you to take my weapon. With Osric dead, it suddenly feels too heavy for me. I think it will do more good with you.
